<div class='allCommunityAnswers'>
<div class='communityAnswer'>
<div class='communityAnswerBody'>
<div class='answererUserIcon'>
<a class="leftAlignedImage userPhoto" href="/user/show/9745602-carmen"><img alt="" src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/users/1337862161i/9745602._UX100_CR0,5,100,100_.jpg" /></a>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerTextContainer'>
<span class='communityAnswererName'>
<a href="/user/show/9745602-carmen">Carmen</a>
</span>
<span class='communityAnswerText'>
<div class='spoiler'>
This answer contains spoilers…
<span class='spoilerAnswerText'>
<a class="jsShowSpoiler spoilerAction">(view spoiler)</a><span class="spoilerContainer" style="display: none">[
  
    The Diaries are written by "Claire" who we initially thought was Amber... <br />Claire's parents were horrible so no sympathy for them! Some confusing diary<a href="#" rel="nofollow noopener">…more</a>
    The Diaries are written by "Claire" who we initially thought was Amber... <br />Claire's parents were horrible so no sympathy for them! Some confusing diary entries where we think Amber is writing them and is jealous of the younger Claire. <br />Amber, who is in the coma, is really Taylor whose parents parented properly. If you recall, Claire is the one who protected Taylor/Amber from the schoolyard bullies. "Claire" stole Taylor's life, burned down her own parents home, and told Taylor (going by Amber) how to get back at Madeline for taking the house Nana had meant to leave to Claire's parents, but had forgotten to write the will. Claire burned down the house and killed her worthless parents so she could be adopted into a loving family and not have to leave Taylor. Claire killed Edward. The reason Taylor/Amber (thought) she killed Claire was to protect Paul, because Claire is so jealous of the love between her and Paul she wants to kill him. Adopting the twins was just the happy side effect, since Claire killed Amber/Taylor's baby by causing the accident. <br />I am certain that Claire did kill Edward and that the bracelet at the end means she's not dead .. so Paul is in danger again.<br />If you all recall, when Amber went for that walk with the dog, David was cold, but Claire's pulse was weak..<a href="#" rel="nofollow noopener">(less)</a>
  
 <a class="jsHideSpoiler spoilerAction">(hide spoiler)</a>]</span>
</span>
</div>
</span>
</div>
